org.jsapar.compose.bean

Class BeanComposer<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jsapar.compose.bean.BeanComposer<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - common base class of all the expected beans. Use Object as base class if there is no common base class for all beans.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventListener, BeanEventListener<T>, Composer, ErrorEventListener

    public class BeanComposer<T>
extends Object
implements Composer, BeanEventListener<T>, ErrorEventListener
    Composer class that composes java beans based on a document or by single lines. The result is that for each bean that was successfully composed, a BeanEvent is generated to all registered BeanEventListener. You can register a BeanEventListener by calling setComposedEventListener(BeanEventListener)
